Description: NextPVR media player client (X11, Debian 11 legacy)
 yauiclient is a 10-foot-UI media player client for NextPVR. This flavour
 targets older Debian-family distributions (Debian 11+, Ubuntu 20.04+,
 Linux Mint 20+) and bundles its own libmpv 0.41 runtime plus FFmpeg 7
 codec libraries in /usr/lib/yauiclient/lib/, isolated from the system
 mpv install. AV1, HEVC and AVC are supported on Intel and AMD GPUs
 through VAAPI; VVC requires the modern (glibc 2.36+) Debian 12 build.
 .
 This package is built on Debian 11 with glibc 2.31 for maximum
 compatibility with older systems. For Debian 12+ / Ubuntu 24.04+ users,
 prefer the yauiclient-x11 package built against the modern toolchain.
 .
 This package installs to /usr/bin/yauiclient and conflicts with the other
 yauiclient flavours; only one can be installed at a time.
